s/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:30:- worker job type\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:38:| `generate_pitches` | `pitches` | `background` | `story.generate_pitches` | `regenerate_pitches` | `StageOperationToolResult` | marks `pitches` in progress and refreshes downstream staleness |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:40:| `generate_character_sheets` | `characters` | `background` | `story.generate_character_sheets` | `regenerate_character_sheet` | `StageOperationToolResult` | marks `characters` in progress and invalidates later planning |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:41:| `refine_character_sheet` | `characters` | `background` | `story.refine_character_sheet` | `refine_character_sheet` | `StageOperationToolResult` | marks `characters` in progress for a revision pass |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:42:| `generate_beat_sheet` | `beats` | `background` | `story.generate_beat_sheet` | `refine_beat_sheet`, `regenerate_beat_sheet` | `StageOperationToolResult` | marks `beats` in progress and invalidates composition work |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:43:| `update_setup_heuristics` | `story_setup` | `direct` | `story.update_setup_heuristics` | `update_story_setup` | `UpdateSetupHeuristicsToolResult` | creates a selected `story_setups` revision, records user-edit and selection events, invalidates downstream stages, cancels active composition/audio jobs |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:44:| `compose_next_segment` | `composition` | `background` | `story.compose_next_segment` | `start_composition` | `CompositionToolResult` | cancels active composition jobs, creates a composition job, seeds a segment row, records initial progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:45:| `rewrite_segments` | `composition` | `background` | `story.rewrite_segments` | `start_composition`, `redirect_composition` | `CompositionToolResult` | cancels active composition jobs, creates a rewrite job, seeds a revised segment row, records initial progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:46:| `estimate_audio_length` | `audio` | `direct` | `story.estimate_audio_length` | `start_audio_generation` | `EstimateAudioLengthToolResult` | computes an estimate from composition segments or story-setup targets without mutating durable state |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:47:| `start_audio_generation` | `audio` | `background` | `story.start_audio_generation` | `start_audio_generation` | `StartAudioGenerationToolResult` | cancels active audio jobs, creates an audio job, records an estimate, marks `audio` in progress |\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:105:[`backend/app/worker/default_handlers.py`](/Users/kevin/code/storyteller/backend/app/worker/default_handlers.py)\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:112:5. Returns the typed result as the durable background job summary.\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:114:That keeps worker dispatch and direct orchestration on the same tool names and result contracts.\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:119:the shared tool registry. That gives the LLM-facing layer the same backend vocabulary that workers\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:133:5. Add tests for registry listing, direct execution, worker dispatch, and prompt exposure if the tool is LLM-facing.\ndocs/story-workflow-tool-registry.md:135:No extra worker-registration code is needed if the new tool definition includes a unique `job_type`.\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:8:from app.worker import JobHandlerRegistry, JobWorker\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:13:    database_path = tmp_path / \"worker-runtime.db\"\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:23:def test_worker_processes_a_registered_job(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:39:            \"worker_id\": context.worker_id,\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:44:    worker = JobWorker(\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:47:        worker_id=\"runtime-worker\",\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:52:    assert worker.run_once() is True\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:60:        \"worker_id\": \"runtime-worker\",\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:65:def test_worker_marks_unknown_job_types_failed(tmp_path: Path) -> None:\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:75:    worker = JobWorker(\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:78:        worker_id=\"runtime-worker\",\nbackend/tests/test_worker_runtime.py:83:    assert worker.run_once() is True\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:12:    resume_stage: 'beats',\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:13:    overall_status: 'in_progress',\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:27:    progress: {\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:30:      in_progress_stages: 1,\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:38:    resume_stage: 'finalize',\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:53:    progress: {\nfrontend/src/pages/home/HomePage.test.tsx:56:      in_progress_stages: 0,\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:21:- `action_type`: stable discriminator such as `select_genre` or `pause_job`.\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:40:| `composition` | `start_composition`, `pause_job`, `resume_job`, `redirect_composition`           | Job control is explicit and stage-bound. Redirects require concrete instructions.                     |\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:41:| `audio`       | `update_audio_settings`, `start_audio_generation`, `pause_job`, `resume_job`     | Audio settings are separate from the command to start generation.                                     |\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:65:- All composition and audio job control actions\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:66:- `redirect_composition`\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:98:      \"action_type\": \"start_composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.md:99:      \"target_stage\": \"composition\",\ndocs/domain-model.md:3:This document defines the durable business objects and workflow rules for a single story-creation session. The goal is to give the backend, frontend, migrations, and later AI orchestration code one shared contract for how a session progresses, pauses, rewinds, and resumes.\ndocs/domain-model.md:23:| `resume_stage` | Earliest stage that still needs work when a session is reopened. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:25:| `overall_status` | Session-level rollup such as `draft`, `in_progress`, `completed`, or `needs_regeneration`. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:32:| `active_composition_job_id` | Current composition job, if writing or rewrite work is running. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:38:`resume_stage` is the key anti-guessing field. The backend computes it from durable stage states so the frontend does not need to infer where to reopen a session by looking at which panels happen to have data.\ndocs/domain-model.md:50:| `workflow_stage_state` | Per-stage state for the session. | `session_id`, `stage`, `status`, `updated_at`, `last_event_id`. | Stored explicitly so resume does not depend on sparse child tables. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:58:| `composition_job` | Parent job record for writing or rewriting text. | status, progress, attempt count, stop reason, current segment pointer. | Not listed in the prompt title, but needed to make `composition_segment` durable and resumable. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:59:| `composition_segment` | One planned or written segment of the story. | segment index, planned summary, text, revision number, superseded segment, status. | Supports interruption, partial persistence, and rewrites of earlier sections. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:60:| `audio_job` | Parent job record for narration generation. | voice, speed, music setting, progress, status, compiled asset pointer. | Audio should be resumable and segment-aware. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:61:| `session_asset` | Durable artifact metadata for session files and exports. | asset kind, object path, MIME type, byte size, checksum, segment index, readiness status. | Covers draft snapshots, composition segments, audio segments, `.docx`, and final audio without scanning object storage. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:62:| `event_log_entry` | Append-only session history. | actor, event type, stage context, payload with `schema_version`, created_at. | Supports replay, resume hydration, debugging, and audit. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:77:| 8 | `composition` | Composition | The current story text is complete enough to hand off to narration. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:95:| `in_progress` | Durable work is actively being produced or updated. | Pitch generation is running, composition is streaming segments, or audio rendering is underway. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:97:| `needs_regeneration` | The stage was completed before, but an upstream change made its accepted output stale. The old output may remain visible for comparison, but it is not the current source of truth. | The user edits characters after a beat sheet exists, so beats, composition, audio, and finalize become stale. |\ndocs/domain-model.md:104:- `in_progress`: at least one stage is `in_progress`, or some stages are completed but the session has not reached a valid finalization state.\ndocs/domain-model.md:112:`genre -> tone -> brief -> pitches -> characters -> beats -> story_setup -> composition -> audio -> finalize`\ndocs/domain-model.md:121:- If all stages are `completed`, `resume_stage` is `finalize`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:123:This is the behavior implemented by the `resolve_resume_stage` helper in both the backend and frontend contract files.\ndocs/domain-model.md:131:| `genre` | `tone`, `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:132:| `tone` | `brief`, `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:133:| `brief` | `pitches`, `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:134:| `pitches` | `characters`, `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:135:| `characters` | `beats`, `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:136:| `beats` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:137:| `story_setup` | `composition`, `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:138:| `composition` | `audio`, `finalize` |\ndocs/domain-model.md:145:- They still influence later composition, but a new pitch or character sheet does not automatically erase the user's preferred target length.\ndocs/domain-model.md:151:- A composition job may move between `in_progress`, paused, resumed, or cancelled states without leaving the `composition` stage.\ndocs/domain-model.md:152:- Partial text is persisted segment by segment so a refresh or crash does not erase progress.\ndocs/domain-model.md:153:- A rewrite request against an earlier segment creates a new `composition_job` or new segment revision rather than mutating history in place.\ndocs/domain-model.md:155:- Any accepted composition rewrite marks `audio` and `finalize` as `needs_regeneration`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:156:- If the user decides the plan itself is wrong, they may navigate back to `beats` or `story_setup`, accept changes there, and let the backend mark `composition` and later stages stale.\ndocs/domain-model.md:163:   - Example: `genre`, `tone`, and `brief` are `completed`; `pitches` is `in_progress`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:164:   - Result: open the session on `resume_stage = pitches`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:166:   - Example: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` were `completed`, then the user edits the beat sheet.\ndocs/domain-model.md:167:   - Result: `composition`, `audio`, and `finalize` become `needs_regeneration`, and `resume_stage = composition`.\ndocs/domain-model.md:170:   - Result: open on `resume_stage = finalize`, but still allow explicit navigation back to earlier stages for edits.\ndocs/domain-model.md:183:- Keep the literal stage-state values stable once they enter database rows or websocket payloads.\ndocs/adr/README.md:9:- `0001-core-runtime-architecture.md`: backend-owned AI calls, durable Postgres session state, file-backed GCS assets, websocket live updates, separate workers for long-running jobs, and soft planning constraints\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:12:    \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:31:    \"start_composition\": \"confirm_first\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:32:    \"pause_job\": \"confirm_first\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:33:    \"resume_job\": \"confirm_first\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:34:    \"redirect_composition\": \"confirm_first\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:148:            \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:419:              \"const\": \"pause_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:420:              \"default\": \"pause_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:426:                \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:478:              \"const\": \"redirect_composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:479:              \"default\": \"redirect_composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:484:              \"const\": \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:485:              \"default\": \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:1173:              \"const\": \"resume_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:1174:              \"default\": \"resume_job\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:1180:                \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:1772:              \"const\": \"start_composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:1773:              \"default\": \"start_composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:1778:              \"const\": \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:1779:              \"default\": \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:2302:            \"composition\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:2316:          \"pause_job\": \"#/$defs/PauseJobAction\",\ndocs/chat-to-ui-actions.schema.json:2317:          \"redirect_composition\": \"#/$defs/Redi